issue.title: Setting a style on an ExcelRow or ExcelRangeRow resets unrelated style objects in an erratic way
Setting a style on an ExcelRow or ExcelRangeRow resets unrelated style objects in an erratic way
Valid excel range reference is considered invalid by EPPlus (ExcelAddress.IsValidAddress function)
issue.body:
### EPPlus usage

Commercial use (I have a commercial license)

### Environment

Windows/.Net framework 4.8

### Epplus version

6.2.9

### Spreadsheet application

Excel

### Description

Using EPPlus for performing calculations based onExcel from a C# application (so we can avoid using Excel server side).

And we're using named cell ranges for referring to particular cell or region in the spreadsheet.
Previously we've been using EPPlus v 4.x.x and i think it worked correctly (however, i might be mistaken)

but after upgrading to 6.2.9 (and 6.2.10 too) EPPlus doesnt consider this reference to be valid excel address:

```
address = "Sheet1!Table313[#All]"
v = OfficeOpenXml.ExcelAddress.IsValidAddress(address)
//v == false
```
the address Sheet1!Table313[#All] refers to an Excel Table together with its headers
this is name manager in Excel, showing the problematic reference
![image](https://github.com/EPPlusSoftware/EPPlus/assets/1706814/1d9a60c1-b8a6-4a59-8736-8190651bda80)

issue.title: Excel Drawings DPI dependent
issue.body:
### EPPlus usage

Commercial use (I have a commercial license)

### Environment

Windows

### Epplus version

6.2.10

### Spreadsheet application

Excel

### Description

Hi, I have an Excel where I use create drawings (most of them rectangles and lines). I use the pixel measurement of my desktop screen that is 1920x1080 with a scale of 100%. And this is the result:
![image](https://github.com/EPPlusSoftware/EPPlus/assets/52248775/3ff520ac-df65-4d5e-9227-309eef1f6d91)

But now I'm using my laptop with a screen of 2880x1800 with a scale of 175% and this is how the drawings look like:
![image](https://github.com/EPPlusSoftware/EPPlus/assets/52248775/2f2b3799-51ab-4ac7-8c0f-0843cfc024eb)

If I change the scale of the laptop to 100% then the drawings are okay. Even if I created the excel with a scale of 175% then close the Excel, change the scale to 100% and open it.

How can I do to obtain the same drawing with a scale different of 100%?

I tried to use a multiplicative factor to the size and position of the drawings but I couldn't make it work.

issue.title: MemoryStreams are not disposed
MemoryStreams are not disposed
Hyperlink subaddress
issue.body:
Excel exposes [Subaddress]( https://learn.microsoft.com/fr-fr/office/vba/api/excel.hyperlink.subaddress) for Hyperlink

EPPlus ignore this value (i have an .xlsx file with this value, and EPPlus get only [Hyperlink.Address](https://learn.microsoft.com/fr-fr/office/vba/api/excel.hyperlink.address)

EPPlus could exposes HyperlinkSubaddress

Fixed in EPPlus 6.2.11 and 7.0.0.
